envisage /ɪnˈvɪzɪdʒ/

(envisaging,envisaged,envisages) 

1. V-T If you envisage something, you imagine that it is true, real, or likely to happen. 设想 

例： He envisages the possibility of establishing direct diplomatic relations in the future. 他设想将来建立直接外交关系的可能性。

